          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "At the hand of The Lich, the world has been plunged into a dark, timeless loop where the hero (and those he meets along the way) are lost without their memories. In a defiant act of survival and a will to rebuild what once was, the hero must fight his way through loops as he attempts to recreate the world in his image, all the while regaining his memories and rebuilding civilisation. Nominated for Best Indie at The Game Awards 2021, ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Loop Hero",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " has landed on Nintendo Switch and it begs to question whether this PC indie darling fares just as well on the hybrid console.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "embed",
